But wait, the test `testMissingNodeForEOFOtherMapper` also exists and expects MissingNode. However, perhaps it is run separately and not part of the same test suite? The JSON output must include only the trigger methods that actually expose the bug. If the bug is defined as the code returning MissingNode when NullNode is expected, then only tests expecting NullNode trigger it. The test expecting MissingNode would pass with the buggy code, so they are not triggers.

